a bunch of red flags.

245
00:15:58,334 --> 00:15:59,494
No, absolutely not.

246
00:15:59,574 --> 00:16:01,453
If you would like, we'll work late.

247
00:16:01,493 --> 00:16:04,772
- Yes, I mean we'll work weekends.
- Weekends are very good for me.

248
00:16:04,852 --> 00:16:07,251
Weekends. Good idea.

249
00:16:07,650 --> 00:16:10,449
Give us plenty of time together,
no distractions.

250
00:16:10,569 --> 00:16:12,169
It is Labor Day.

251
00:16:15,847 --> 00:16:17,326
I got an idea.

252
00:16:19,925 --> 00:16:23,524
How would you two like to come
to my house at the beach?

253
00:16:23,644 --> 00:16:24,883
- Me?
- Us?

254
00:16:24,963 --> 00:16:26,643
Yeah. Hampton Island.

255
00:16:26,723 --> 00:16:29,401
Ever been there? Well, you will love it.

256
00:16:29,481 --> 00:16:31,720
When we're not working,
there are distractions.

257
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:34,639
There are women, swimming,
boating, famous people.

258
00:16:37,878 --> 00:16:39,237
Well?

259
00:16:39,277 --> 00:16:40,317
- Love to!
- Okay.

260
00:16:40,397 --> 00:16:42,196
Good! It's settled.

261
00:16:42,836 --> 00:16:45,795
We are going to have a good time,
I guarantee.

262
00:16:45,875 --> 00:16:47,874
My secretary will write down
the directions...

263
00:16:47,914 --> 00:16:50,193
- give you the ferry schedule.
- The ferry schedule?

264
00:16:50,273 --> 00:16:53,551
It's the only way to get there,
unless you have a boat. I don't know.

265
00:16:53,631 --> 00:16:55,391
I have never even been on a boat.

266
00:16:55,471 --> 00:16:57,870
I was once on the Staten Island Ferry
with my folks...

267
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:01,748
Whatever. You come out Friday night,
you'll have a great time, I guarantee it.

268
00:17:01,788 --> 00:17:04,787
I'll even drive you back to the city myself
on Monday. Okay?

269
00:17:04,867 --> 00:17:06,986
We don't know what to say, Bernie.

270
00:17:07,746 --> 00:17:09,945
You don't have to say anything.

271
00:17:10,105 --> 00:17:12,943
If you two uncovered what I think
you uncovered...

272
00:17:13,263 --> 00:17:16,742
old Bernie here owes you both a great deal.
I mean it sincerely.

273
00:17:16,822 --> 00:17:19,021
Now get out of here. Go on.

274
00:17:20,980 --> 00:17:22,419
He loves us.

275
00:17:22,739 --> 00:17:26,658
The man absolutely loves us.

276
00:17:28,777 --> 00:17:30,256
You have to kill them, Vito.

277
00:17:41,811 --> 00:17:44,050
Let me explain something to you.

278
00:17:44,810 --> 00:17:48,569
We don't do that anymore.
We are a corporation now.

279
00:17:49,528 --> 00:17:51,967
We are in the market. We invest.

280
00:17:52,007 --> 00:17:55,806
Real estate. Car rentals. Parking lots.

281
00:17:57,165 --> 00:17:59,404
Parking lots. That's good.

282
00:18:00,124 --> 00:18:03,043
- I understand that, but...
- Didn't I order the walnut dressing?

283
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:05,442
- Yes, you did.
- Taste that.

284
00:18:07,081 --> 00:18:10,160
Does that taste
anything like walnut dressing? Tell me.

285
00:18:10,879 --> 00:18:13,198
This is the raspberry vinaigrette.

286
00:18:13,998 --> 00:18:16,677
Should I have Paulie go
and talk to the chef?

287
00:18:19,236 --> 00:18:22,794
This goddamn raspberry vinaigrette...

288
00:18:26,953 --> 00:18:28,512
Excuse me, Vito.

289
00:18:36,948 --> 00:18:39,667
I know how important food is to you,
I mean...

290
00:18:40,987 --> 00:18:42,866
But we've got a problem here.

291
00:18:43,706 --> 00:18:46,225
I give problems. I don't get problems.

292
00:18:51,582 --> 00:18:53,941
How do you propose to handle it?

293
00:18:53,981 --> 00:18:57,060
Let's make it a murder-suicide job. All right?

294
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:59,059
Okay, gentlemen?

295
00:18:59,459 --> 00:19:02,898
I'll plant some money, fake a note,
and they can take the rap and...

296
00:19:02,978 --> 00:19:05,776
I won't even have to change the books.

297
00:19:06,096 --> 00:19:07,776
What do you think?

298
00:19:11,854 --> 00:19:14,173
I like it. It's creative.

299
00:19:17,891 --> 00:19:20,650
I am a little rusty. But it'll come back to me.

300
00:19:26,728 --> 00:19:27,847
Okay.

301
00:19:30,526 --> 00:19:33,165
- Do it.
- This is good.

302
00:19:33,285 --> 00:19:35,844
I mean this is really good. Good.

303
00:19:37,963 --> 00:19:41,402
I think we are going to have some fun.

304
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:49,318
- I have to get going. I really do.
- What, no dessert?

305
00:19:49,838 --> 00:19:52,877
They do a wonderful crème brûlée here.
It's delicious.

306
00:19:53,157 --> 00:19:56,715
No, gentlemen, I really must be going.
Thanks for dinner, Vito.

307
00:20:03,393 --> 00:20:05,552
I got to go powder my nose.

308
00:20:22,265 --> 00:20:24,544
Forget the accident with the two guys.

309
00:20:24,824 --> 00:20:26,063
Take care of Lomax.

310
00:20:27,782 --> 00:20:28,982
He's getting too careless...

311
00:20:30,661 --> 00:20:31,741
too greedy.

312
00:20:34,779 --> 00:20:36,139
Besides...

313
00:20:37,538 --> 00:20:39,498
he's screwing my girlfriend.

314
00:20:39,737 --> 00:20:42,576
But you said we were going to
spend the weekend at the beach!

315
00:20:42,656 --> 00:20:45,575
You heard the conversation.
What am I supposed to do about it?

316
00:20:45,615 --> 00:20:46,615
- Bernie.
- What?

317
00:20:46,695 --> 00:20:50,333
I told Vito I was going to spend
some time with my mother!

318
00:20:57,090 --> 00:20:58,929
I have to see you, Bernie.

319
00:21:00,169 --> 00:21:01,368
Cut it out.

320
00:21:02,008 --> 00:21:04,847
- What's wrong with you? Wait a minute.
- What?

321
00:21:04,927 --> 00:21:06,806
- I have an idea.
- What?

322
00:21:06,886 --> 00:21:09,885
You are on, 9:00 Friday night.
I'll be at the apartment.

323
00:21:09,965 --> 00:21:11,844
Just use your key. All right?

324
00:21:12,644 --> 00:21:14,803
I'll wear something special.

325
00:21:15,842 --> 00:21:18,201
I bet you never had sweet and sour
matzo balls before.

326
00:21:18,281 --> 00:21:19,281
No.

327
00:21:22,120 --> 00:21:24,999
- I am glad you finally asked me out.
- You are?

328
00:21:26,278 --> 00:21:28,437
I wish you had asked me out sooner.

329
00:21:28,677 --> 00:21:31,876
Today was my last day at work.
I am going back to college.

330
00:21:32,915 --> 00:21:35,154
We could still have
this weekend together, right?

331
00:21:35,234 --> 00:21:37,194
I am spending it with my folks.

332
00:21:37,274 --> 00:21:39,713
- Are your folks in town?
- No.

333
00:21:40,472 --> 00:21:44,071
Is this the intimate evening
I promised you, or what?

334
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:47,669
You think there's anywhere we could go
to just sit and talk...

335
00:21:47,749 --> 00:21:50,988
and not have to scream
and get run over by garbage trucks?

336
00:21:51,068 --> 00:21:52,947
- Hey, want to throw her in?
- How you doing?

337
00:21:53,027 --> 00:21:56,186
I'd invite you to my apartment,
but I have five roommates.

338
00:21:56,266 --> 00:21:58,625
And they are all at home
doing their hair right now.

339
00:21:58,705 --> 00:22:02,703
That's a lot of hair. But it's clean. I like that.

340
00:22:03,303 --> 00:22:07,221
It's either that or living with my parents,
and I don't think that's a good idea.

341
00:22:07,301 --> 00:22:10,740
I can't blame you. Who'd want
to live with their folks? That's no good.

342
00:22:10,820 --> 00:22:13,858
- Do you have any roommates?
- No. Roommates? No. None.

343
00:22:14,218 --> 00:22:15,698
Why don't we go to your place?

344
00:22:15,778 --> 00:22:19,376
Come on, baby. You're not a woman.
Are you? Tell me the truth.

345
00:22:25,094 --> 00:22:26,373
Okay.

346
00:22:38,448 --> 00:22:40,327
Why are you tiptoeing?

347
00:22:41,847 --> 00:22:43,166
Because...

348
00:22:46,485 --> 00:22:50,123
the people who live downstairs,
they're very light sleepers.

349
00:22:51,363 --> 00:22:53,762
They get angry when I walk.

350
00:22:54,961 --> 00:22:56,880
Why are you whispering?

351
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,999
- Am I?
- Yes.

352
00:23:00,599 --> 00:23:04,917
I am. That's because of the walls.
They are too thin.

353
00:23:05,917 --> 00:23:09,555
- Make yourself at home.
- Thank you.

354
00:23:22,150 --> 00:23:26,108
Look at this teak.
I mean this whole apartment.

355
00:23:26,628 --> 00:23:28,827
Sort of '60s style.

356
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:31,906
Yeah. I know.
I've been meaning to redo that for years.

357
00:23:31,986 --> 00:23:35,065
No, I love it. I mean, it's very hip.

358
00:23:36,464 --> 00:23:38,743
I think you have done the place beautifully.

359
00:23:38,823 --> 00:23:41,062
I like it. It's home.

360
00:23:41,142 --> 00:23:44,061
You know, it's a side of you
I never would have expected.

361
00:23:44,101 --> 00:23:45,660
I'm very impressed.

362
00:23:45,740 --> 00:23:47,379
- Are you?
- Yeah.

363
00:23:48,499 --> 00:23:49,858
About what?

364
00:23:50,258 --> 00:23:53,057
This apartment has got to be expensive.

365
00:23:53,137 --> 00:23:55,896
So obviously you could have taken me
to some flash restaurant instead of that...

366
00:23:56,016 --> 00:23:58,535
Is "dump" the word you are groping for?

367
00:23:59,055 --> 00:24:01,134
You didn't like Hymie's Hunan?

368
00:24:01,734 --> 00:24:04,852
- It's a four-star dive.
- It was great. I loved it.

369
00:24:04,932 --> 00:24:08,291
It's just that some men
would try to impress women by...

370
00:24:08,371 --> 00:24:10,490
pretending to be something they are not.

371
00:24:10,570 --> 00:24:14,048
I absolutely agree. That's a terrible way
to begin a relationship.

372
00:24:14,128 --> 00:24:16,887
Pretending to be something you are not.

373
00:24:17,007 --> 00:24:18,247
Oh, God.

374
00:24:18,487 --> 00:24:21,445
You don't have to answer this
if you don't want to...

375
00:24:21,525 --> 00:24:24,204
but how do you afford a place like this?

376
00:24:26,443 --> 00:24:28,602
I don't like to brag.

377
00:24:28,802 --> 00:24:31,961
I just feel uncomfortable
showing off my money...

378
00:24:32,041 --> 00:24:36,199
but I've made some wise investments.
I dabble in the stock market.

379
00:24:36,439 --> 00:24:40,557
And of course my parents
were rather well off.

380
00:24:41,197 --> 00:24:42,916
Do you want to sit?

381
00:24:45,995 --> 00:24:47,634
They passed away?

382
00:24:48,714 --> 00:24:49,754
Yes.

383
00:24:49,914 --> 00:24:51,953
They must have been young.

384
00:24:52,752 --> 00:24:54,032
Oh, yeah.

385
00:24:54,312 --> 00:24:56,911
I feel I can trust you.

386
00:24:58,910 --> 00:25:01,149
They were in a train accident.

387
00:25:01,349 --> 00:25:03,788
Yeah, I mean I don't know
what it was with trains...

388
00:25:03,868 --> 00:25:07,466
but they just always liked to travel in trains.

389
00:25:08,466 --> 00:25:09,825
I am sorry.

390
00:25:10,865 --> 00:25:13,064
- How awful for you.
- Yeah.

391
00:25:14,983 --> 00:25:19,581
You know, I always thought trains
were so much safer than planes.

392
00:25:20,221 --> 00:25:23,540
Well, actually, a plane...

393
00:25:24,619 --> 00:25:26,418
fell on the train.

394
00:25:52,288 --> 00:25:53,807
- Richard.
- Gwen.

395
00:25:56,286 --> 00:26:00,124
There's a man in his underwear
in your kitchen.

396
00:26:01,044 --> 00:26:02,923
He's... He's with me.

397
00:26:05,962 --> 00:26:08,241
He's my butler. But...

398
00:26:08,841 --> 00:26:11,440
- You have a butler?
- Yeah. Don't get him started.

399
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:14,838
He'll just go away if you just be quiet.

400
00:26:23,235 --> 00:26:25,434
Sorry. I didn't realize you had company.

401
00:26:25,514 --> 00:26:27,193
Good evening, young lady.

402
00:26:27,273 --> 00:26:29,312
That's all right, Monroe.

403
00:26:32,031 --> 00:26:36,589
Yes, will you, please, just go lay out
my navy blue suit for the morning?

404
00:26:36,669 --> 00:26:37,749
Please.

405
00:26:37,829 --> 00:26:40,188
- How about if I lay you out?
- Very well.

406
00:26:45,106 --> 00:26:48,544
- You let your butler talk to you like that?
- Well, he is a vet.

407
00:26:48,624 --> 00:26:50,863
He has got a steel plate in his head.

408
00:26:52,822 --> 00:26:55,141
Gwen, it's not what you think.

409
00:26:55,661 --> 00:26:57,341
Goodbye, Richard.

410
00:27:24,449 --> 00:27:25,489
I'll grab the bow line.

411
00:27:25,569 --> 00:27:28,648
- Hey, Skeet. How are you doing?
- Hey, Mr. Lomax.

412
00:27:28,728 --> 00:27:31,606
Here you go, my friend.
Buy yourself a girlfriend.

413
00:27:32,726 --> 00:27:34,485
Where have you been, Candy?

414
00:27:35,445 --> 00:27:38,443
- Hey, Bernie. How about a drink?
- A little bit later.

415
00:27:41,642 --> 00:27:44,961
- Yo, Bernie. The cocktail flag is up.
- A little bit later.

416
00:27:45,041 --> 00:27:47,800
Booze and women.
That is my lifestyle and I love it!

417
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:49,159
And I!

418
00:28:25,744 --> 00:28:28,543
- George, how are you?
- Nice to see you, Mr. Lomax.

419
00:28:31,821 --> 00:28:34,020
What are you doing here?
I fired you last week.

420
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:35,660
- I just want my $90, okay?
- Bullshit!

421
00:28:35,740 --> 00:28:38,099
You drank my liquor
and the toilets still don't work.

422
00:28:38,179 --> 00:28:40,018
I don't want to see you.

423
00:28:40,258 --> 00:28:41,617
Get out of here!

424
00:28:42,297 --> 00:28:44,656
You come back again,
I am going to call the cops!

425
00:28:44,736 --> 00:28:46,495
You son of a bitch.

426
00:28:49,454 --> 00:28:53,292
- I am sorry. I think she needs a little B-12.
- Whatever.

427
00:28:53,372 --> 00:28:56,211
{y:i}This is Bernie. Leave a message,
{y:i}I'll get right back to you.

428
00:28:56,291 --> 00:28:58,250
- Goodbye, Mr. Lomax.
- Bye.

429
00:28:58,330 --> 00:28:59,890
Hello?

430
00:29:00,409 --> 00:29:03,688
Hey, Lomax. It's Paulie.
I just got to the island.

431
00:29:04,048 --> 00:29:05,087
You are early.

432
00:29:05,167 --> 00:29:07,526
Those schmucks are not coming
until the 6:00 ferry...

433
00:29:07,606 --> 00:29:10,085
- and I still have to plant the note.
- Yeah.

434
00:29:10,205 --> 00:29:11,485
So where is your house?

435
00:29:11,525 --> 00:29:13,604
It's on the point, top of the dune.

436
00:29:13,684 --> 00:29:16,523
Look, Paulie,
don't kill them while I am around.

437
00:29:16,563 --> 00:29:18,682
Bernie, we are on a phone here.

438
00:29:18,762 --> 00:29:20,521
Right. You are right. Okay, I am sorry.

439
00:29:20,601 --> 00:29:23,920
The point is, I just want to be
back in New York with an alibi, okay?

440
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:25,999
Yeah. Don't worry about it.

441
00:29:37,074 --> 00:29:38,554
Oh, God!

442
00:29:40,433 --> 00:29:42,032
Rich. It is leaving. Come on!

443
00:29:42,112 --> 00:29:44,591
I told you we should've taken
a taxi from the station.

444
00:29:44,631 --> 00:29:47,590
- There's another boat in a half hour.
- We'll miss the parties.

445
00:29:47,670 --> 00:29:49,629
We got it. Excuse me.

446
00:29:49,669 --> 00:29:51,988
- Sorry.
- Coming through.

447
00:29:52,068 --> 00:29:55,507
Don't be ridiculous! What are you doing?
We are not jumping on this boat!

448
00:29:55,587 --> 00:29:56,946
- Do you hear me?
- Here we go!

449
00:29:57,026 --> 00:30:00,065
Listen to me, Larry, we are not
jumping on this boat!

450
00:30:00,145 --> 00:30:02,504
- Jesus Christ! My elbow!
- Piece of cake!

451
00:30:04,903 --> 00:30:06,422
Thanks, pal.

452
00:30:09,141 --> 00:30:12,460
This ferry isn't leaving. It's docking.

453
00:30:13,779 --> 00:30:15,858
- Okay. We're early.
- You schmuck.

454
00:30:30,612 --> 00:30:33,171
- What is your name?
- What is your name?

455
00:30:33,291 --> 00:30:35,370
- Larry.
- Hi, Larry. I am Michelle.

456
00:30:35,730 --> 00:30:38,968
Come on! Lighten up there, Rich!
We are on our way!

457
00:30:39,008 --> 00:30:42,727
I am so depressed.
I made a fool out of myself last night.

458
00:30:42,807 --> 00:30:43,886
Of course you did.

459
00:30:43,966 --> 00:30:46,445
- I should've stayed home.
- What are you talking about?

460
00:30:46,525 --> 00:30:50,084
We've been summoned to the mountain top.
This is good for your career.

461
00:30:50,164 --> 00:30:54,082
You know, by the time this weekend is over,
I promise you won't even remember...

462
00:30:54,162 --> 00:30:57,201
what's-her-name's name.
I'll get you a drink. Come on.

463
00:30:57,281 --> 00:30:59,400
Look, I'll see you later.

464
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,959
Goodbye, young man. Nice talking to you.

465
00:31:15,273 --> 00:31:17,512
That is good. This is very good.

466
00:31:23,790 --> 00:31:26,109
- I did not hear you come in.
- I know.

467
00:31:26,949 --> 00:31:28,308
I am real good at that.

468
00:31:28,348 --> 00:31:30,947
- I told you the guys aren't here yet, didn't I?
- You did.

469
00:31:31,027 --> 00:31:32,786
- Good.
- Quite a shack you have here.

470
00:31:32,866 --> 00:31:34,306
It's home.

471
00:31:35,585 --> 00:31:37,224
Can I have a cigarette?

472
00:31:39,064 --> 00:31:40,143
Cigarette.

473
00:31:42,422 --> 00:31:43,542
Sure.

474
00:31:48,220 --> 00:31:49,819
What was...

475
00:31:59,455 --> 00:32:01,494
Quite a ride, huh, Bern?

476
00:32:20,326 --> 00:32:22,485
Glorious day out, or what?

477
00:32:22,525 --> 00:32:24,005
Where's Bernie?

478
00:32:24,085 --> 00:32:28,323
I got it right here. It says it's the last house
on the point, top of the dune.

479
00:32:29,443 --> 00:32:33,001
Pardon me, Monsignor, sir, could you
tell me where the top of the dune is?

480
00:32:33,081 --> 00:32:36,600
- Bless you, my son.
- Thank you, Father.

481
00:32:36,919 --> 00:32:39,079
Look, we'll find it. Okay.

482
00:32:39,758 --> 00:32:42,557
- You know, it's an island, right?
- How hard can it be?

483
00:32:43,877 --> 00:32:45,956
Excuse me. Is this the way to...

484
00:33:01,109 --> 00:33:04,388
- Yo, is this Bernie Lomax's house?
- Sure is.

485
00:33:04,868 --> 00:33:06,027
