crumpled up on my floor in the morning.

728
00:47:03,679 --> 00:47:05,759
Polyester doesn't crumple.

729
00:47:08,997 --> 00:47:11,556
- Here we go. That's it, Bernie.
- Hi, Bernie.

730
00:47:12,316 --> 00:47:14,515
- Just like last week, huh?
- Come on.

731
00:47:17,474 --> 00:47:19,913
All right. Okay.

732
00:47:20,193 --> 00:47:24,151
Look me in the eye. $50,000.

733
00:47:24,231 --> 00:47:27,909
Yes! I knew it! Thank you, Bernie!

734
00:47:27,989 --> 00:47:31,108
Thank you so much. This guy is like family.

735
00:47:31,188 --> 00:47:32,587
You are beautiful!

736
00:47:33,187 --> 00:47:35,666
Grab him. Larry.

737
00:47:37,745 --> 00:47:39,864
- Jesus.
- Oh, God.

738
00:47:40,544 --> 00:47:44,023
- Hi, boys. Great view.
- Hello, there. How are you?

739
00:47:47,101 --> 00:47:48,781
I give it an 8.3.

740
00:47:50,500 --> 00:47:52,859
We can't just leave him there, you know.

741
00:48:02,695 --> 00:48:07,133
Girl. Beach. Sand. Surf. Moonlight.
Did you ever see {y:i}Here to Eternity?

742
00:48:10,891 --> 00:48:12,971
You are right. We better get him.

743
00:48:13,650 --> 00:48:16,889
- Thirty minutes. Then we call the cops.
- Not a second more.

744
00:48:18,728 --> 00:48:19,848
Ladies, how are you?

745
00:48:30,883 --> 00:48:31,763
Hi.

746
00:48:30,883 --> 00:48:31,763
Hi.

747
00:48:40,999 --> 00:48:43,238
Are we allowed to talk or anything?

748
00:48:47,396 --> 00:48:49,595
Why did you leave the party?

749
00:48:49,675 --> 00:48:52,954
I just don't feel comfortable
with most of those people.

750
00:48:53,034 --> 00:48:57,792
I don't really know any of those people.
I just know, knew, know Bernie.

751
00:48:58,432 --> 00:49:01,231
Besides, I figure
I can thank Bernie tomorrow.

752
00:49:01,311 --> 00:49:03,030
When there's more privacy.

753
00:49:04,509 --> 00:49:07,868
- Where are we going?
- There's a beautiful view from up there.

754
00:49:08,907 --> 00:49:09,947
Great.

755
00:49:18,064 --> 00:49:20,263
Ever been in a lighthouse before?

756
00:49:20,303 --> 00:49:23,181
No, this is my first time. This is great.

757
00:49:23,661 --> 00:49:27,780
Does anybody live up there?
A lighthouse keeper or someone?

758
00:49:27,860 --> 00:49:30,418
No, It's all automated now. Come on.

759
00:49:33,257 --> 00:49:36,256
That takes some of the romance out of it.

760
00:49:37,775 --> 00:49:38,935
Does it?

761
00:49:58,807 --> 00:50:00,366
- You all right?
- Yeah.

762
00:50:03,285 --> 00:50:05,684
You're right. This is beautiful.

763
00:50:07,243 --> 00:50:10,322
My God.
You can see the whole island from up here.

764
00:50:14,680 --> 00:50:16,679
I've always wondered
how these things work.

765
00:50:16,759 --> 00:50:18,119
Richard, don't.

766
00:50:18,878 --> 00:50:21,237
- I can't see.
- Watch out for the trap...

767
00:50:23,077 --> 00:50:24,076
door.

768
00:50:29,594 --> 00:50:30,833
Oh, my God.

769
00:50:38,750 --> 00:50:40,469
- That one works.
- Richard.

770
00:50:41,589 --> 00:50:43,308
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

771
00:50:43,388 --> 00:50:45,507
- Are you sure?
- I fell down a couple of stairs.

772
00:50:45,587 --> 00:50:47,426
- Anything broken?
- Nothing's broken.

773
00:50:47,506 --> 00:50:50,305
- Are you sure?
- A little pain, but I'm all right.

774
00:50:50,385 --> 00:50:52,464
- I'm fine. How are you?
- I'm good.

775
00:50:52,824 --> 00:50:54,344
Here. Hold on.

776
00:50:54,424 --> 00:50:56,543
The good news is, I can see again.

777
00:51:00,461 --> 00:51:03,020
- I'm so sorry, Richard.
- No, it's okay, really.

778
00:51:03,100 --> 00:51:04,979
I've always wanted a limp.

779
00:51:05,619 --> 00:51:07,658
I must thank you.
This has been a great date.

780
00:51:07,738 --> 00:51:09,857
I hope my major medical covers it.

781
00:51:10,377 --> 00:51:11,377
What?

782
00:51:12,336 --> 00:51:15,895
I'm sorry. I don't mean to laugh...

783
00:51:16,374 --> 00:51:20,013
but the look on your face
when you fell through the trapdoor.

784
00:51:20,253 --> 00:51:22,212
I think I've got a cracked rib.

785
00:51:22,292 --> 00:51:25,091
- Do you want to sit down?
- No.

786
00:51:25,171 --> 00:51:29,009
No, I better not. The way things are going,
I'm gonna break my ass.

787
00:51:29,409 --> 00:51:31,008
You'll be okay.

788
00:51:59,197 --> 00:52:02,115
I've had a crush on you
since the first day I saw you at work.

789
00:52:02,195 --> 00:52:03,635
I'm crazy about you.

790
00:52:07,073 --> 00:52:08,513
This is so right.

791
00:52:10,592 --> 00:52:13,751
Oh, my God. This can't be happening to me.

792
00:52:13,831 --> 00:52:17,589
It's happening to both of us.
You're right. It's so right.

793
00:52:17,669 --> 00:52:20,348
No. This isn't right, it's all wrong.
Not here in the sand.

794
00:52:20,428 --> 00:52:21,867
- What?
- You deserve more than this.

795
00:52:21,947 --> 00:52:24,666
You need music, flowers, candles.
You need...

796
00:52:26,265 --> 00:52:28,265
You need to get out of here.

797
00:52:28,345 --> 00:52:31,303
- Are you kidding me?
- No, I'm serious. You could catch a cold.

798
00:52:31,343 --> 00:52:33,342
- Where do you live?
- Dune Walk.

799
00:52:51,495 --> 00:52:52,974
Are you dead, too?

800
00:52:54,134 --> 00:52:55,893
Mister? Hello?

801
00:52:56,453 --> 00:52:58,732
Oh, Jesus. What is it with this place?

802
00:53:01,491 --> 00:53:03,770
How are you? Party's over.
You have to go home now.

803
00:53:03,850 --> 00:53:05,569
- Where's Bernie?
- He's swimming.

804
00:53:05,649 --> 00:53:08,368
I had a wonderful time.
I'm sorry I had to leave so early.

805
00:53:08,408 --> 00:53:10,967
Have fun. See you at the next one. Larry!

806
00:53:20,843 --> 00:53:22,562
Larry, are you in there?

807
00:53:22,682 --> 00:53:25,561
- Come on out, Lar. Right now.
- Go away.

808
00:53:25,641 --> 00:53:27,200
I need to talk to you.

809
00:53:27,680 --> 00:53:29,679
Can you just give me 30 seconds?

810
00:53:30,719 --> 00:53:32,918
Bernie is waiting for us.

811
00:53:34,797 --> 00:53:38,475
- Look, Bernie isn't going anywhere, okay?
- I need you, Lar.

812
00:53:48,751 --> 00:53:49,951
Bernie, he needs you, too.

813
00:53:50,111 --> 00:53:51,070
Unbelievable.

814
00:54:02,186 --> 00:54:05,464
How am I supposed to know
that the tide is gonna come up that high?

815
00:54:05,504 --> 00:54:07,463
I don't want to talk about it.

816
00:54:07,543 --> 00:54:10,062
I don't understand why this is becoming
all my fault.

817
00:54:11,142 --> 00:54:13,821
- Did you invite somebody over?
- Of course not.

818
00:54:13,901 --> 00:54:14,980
Somebody's here.

819
00:54:15,060 --> 00:54:17,819
Let's just shove him in the bedroom,
we'll say he's sleeping.

820
00:54:18,379 --> 00:54:20,898
Bernie, you cheat.

821
00:54:21,218 --> 00:54:22,457
Two-timer.

822
00:54:29,894 --> 00:54:31,293
Bernie, open up.

823
00:54:34,372 --> 00:54:35,932
Darn you, Bernie.

824
00:54:36,611 --> 00:54:38,171
Don't do this to me.

825
00:54:40,170 --> 00:54:42,809
Where the hell are you, you son of a bitch?

826
00:54:42,969 --> 00:54:45,608
I got you now, you two-timing bastard.

827
00:54:48,166 --> 00:54:51,045
Who the hell are you? Where's Bernie?

828
00:54:51,565 --> 00:54:53,604
We're Bernie's houseguests. Who are you?

829
00:54:53,684 --> 00:54:55,044
I'm his woman.

830
00:54:56,043 --> 00:54:59,522
And I'll kill him if he's cheating on me.
Now, where the hell is he?

831
00:54:59,602 --> 00:55:02,081
And don't try to cover up for him, either.

832
00:55:02,640 --> 00:55:04,959
- He's not here.
- Haven't seen him.

833
00:55:05,039 --> 00:55:06,599
I don't believe you.

834
00:55:07,798 --> 00:55:09,997
I'm gonna tear this place apart.

835
00:55:16,275 --> 00:55:18,754
- That's his woman?
- I guess so.

836
00:55:29,829 --> 00:55:31,588
Where the hell is he?

837
00:55:31,668 --> 00:55:34,347
- He's in the bedroom.
- Is that so?

838
00:55:35,867 --> 00:55:37,346
He better be alone.

839
00:55:39,625 --> 00:55:40,945
God damn it.

840
00:55:41,024 --> 00:55:42,544
Fun while it lasted, huh?

841
00:55:42,624 --> 00:55:45,783
What difference does it make,
we might as well get this over with.

842
00:55:45,822 --> 00:55:49,021
This is good. She discovers the body,
she calls the police.

843
00:55:49,101 --> 00:55:51,060
Fix me a drink, will you?

844
00:55:51,660 --> 00:55:53,579
I hate it when they scream.

845
00:56:18,449 --> 00:56:19,888
Oh, no!

846
00:56:31,963 --> 00:56:34,562
What gives? She has been up there, what,
10, 15 minutes?

847
00:56:34,922 --> 00:56:36,521
I don't get it.

848
00:57:07,109 --> 00:57:08,868
Got a little scotch?

849
00:57:10,907 --> 00:57:11,987
Sure.

850
00:57:24,302 --> 00:57:28,020
- Did everything go okay up there?
- Never been better.

851
00:57:33,178 --> 00:57:34,297
Good.

852
00:57:44,813 --> 00:57:48,731
How do you like that?
The guy gets laid more dead than I do alive.

853
00:57:49,811 --> 00:57:51,370
No, she couldn't have.

854
00:57:52,730 --> 00:57:54,169
He couldn't have.

855
00:57:54,849 --> 00:57:57,128
I get yelled at when I just lay there.

856
00:58:21,598 --> 00:58:26,116
Vito, I'm telling you, Lomax is alive.
She was with him for at least half an hour...

857
00:58:26,516 --> 00:58:29,874
- in the bedroom.
{y:i}- What were they doing in the bedroom?

858
00:58:29,954 --> 00:58:31,913
I'd rather not say.

859
00:58:31,953 --> 00:58:34,073
{y:i}What the hell happened to Paulie?

860
00:58:34,153 --> 00:58:37,591
Yeah, maybe Paulie
is rustier than we thought, huh?

861
00:58:39,990 --> 00:58:43,829
- What a night.
- Great, isn't it? It isn't over yet.

862
00:58:44,068 --> 00:58:47,147
It is for me. I'm dead. No offense, Bernie.

863
00:58:47,947 --> 00:58:49,786
I just gotta lie down for a minute.

864
00:58:49,866 --> 00:58:53,664
Suit yourself. Whatever you like.
I'm going on to find the next party.

865
00:58:54,144 --> 00:58:57,383
- Just wake me up when you get back.
- Okay, sure.

866
00:58:57,423 --> 00:58:59,862
- Whatever you like.
- Because I got to call the cops.

867
00:58:59,942 --> 00:59:03,061
- Of course you do. In the morning.
- I need a clear head.

868
00:59:03,460 --> 00:59:04,900
Good night, buddy.

869
00:59:05,540 --> 00:59:08,218
Don't forget. Wake me up.

870
00:59:14,336 --> 00:59:17,375
I made these a little sweeter this time.
Okay, Bernie?

871
00:59:18,254 --> 00:59:20,053
God, it's glorious out, huh?

872
00:59:21,613 --> 00:59:23,212
Here we go, my friend.

873
00:59:24,452 --> 00:59:25,931
This should do it.

874
00:59:28,050 --> 00:59:29,050
Okay.

875
00:59:29,450 --> 00:59:31,249
How did you deal with?

876
00:59:32,328 --> 00:59:35,327
Oriental? I think I own that one.

877
00:59:36,127 --> 00:59:37,486
With hotel.

878
00:59:38,886 --> 00:59:40,525
$550.

879
00:59:40,565 --> 00:59:42,724
Give me $600, we'll call it square.

880
00:59:42,804 --> 00:59:44,483
Hey, Bernie, Larry.

881
00:59:44,603 --> 00:59:47,162
Great party last night, Bernie.
Your best ever.

882
00:59:47,242 --> 00:59:49,601
Ladies. Hello. How are you today?

883
00:59:49,681 --> 00:59:50,721
- Great.
- Fine.

884
00:59:50,801 --> 00:59:54,199
- Are we doing it again today?
- Absolutely. You know we are.

885
00:59:54,239 --> 00:59:56,438
- Great. We'll see you later, guys.
- Bye-bye.

886
00:59:56,518 --> 00:59:58,797
Bye-bye, ladies. We'll see you later.

887
00:59:58,957 --> 01:00:00,637
Is this great or what?

888
01:00:01,916 --> 01:00:03,915
Okay, coming out. My turn.

889
01:00:04,235 --> 01:00:05,435
Shooter now.

890
01:00:06,034 --> 01:00:08,913
Yes! Free parking. $500 for me.

891
01:00:14,511 --> 01:00:15,630
Bastard!

892
01:00:21,308 --> 01:00:24,787
I own it. Okay, that is $24...

893
01:00:24,907 --> 01:00:27,905
I own them all. $46, my friend. Call it $50.

894
01:00:28,225 --> 01:00:30,784
Thank you. My turn. Here we go.

895
01:00:30,864 --> 01:00:32,463
Lucky seven coming out.

896
01:00:32,663 --> 01:00:33,663
Shit.

897
01:00:34,543 --> 01:00:38,701
One more you get out of jail free.
All right. Fine. Your turn. I'll roll.

898
01:00:38,781 --> 01:00:40,420
Here we go. Coming out.

899
01:00:42,419 --> 01:00:43,779
Community Chest.

900
01:00:45,378 --> 01:00:47,497
Second prize in a beauty contest.

901
01:00:47,977 --> 01:00:50,936
- What are you doing?
- Playing Monopoly. You want to play?

902
01:00:50,976 --> 01:00:53,055
- No.
- Here we go.

903
01:00:53,815 --> 01:00:55,814
- How did he get down here?
- He walked.

904
01:00:55,894 --> 01:00:57,253
- He walked?
- Say good morning.

905
01:00:58,013 --> 01:01:00,972
Oh, God. You're just a sick man, Larry.

906
01:01:01,611 --> 01:01:04,730
- What time is it?
- It's 11:30.

907
01:01:05,370 --> 01:01:06,529
11:30?

908
01:01:07,209 --> 01:01:09,888
You let me sleep till 11:30? I have...

909
01:01:11,247 --> 01:01:13,646
- When did you get a Rolex?
- Oh, this.

910
01:01:16,485 --> 01:01:19,244
- Good God!
- He didn't need it anymore.

911
01:01:19,644 --> 01:01:22,643
That's it. We're gonna go to jail.
They're gonna arrest us.

912
01:01:22,683 --> 01:01:26,361
- I'm calling the cops.
- I wanted to call them yesterday, my friend.

913
01:01:27,321 --> 01:01:29,440
He's very upset. Richard, look.

914
01:01:29,720 --> 01:01:33,718
Let me just say one thing here.
There's no reason to get pissy about this.

915
01:01:36,557 --> 01:01:37,676
Hello.

916
01:01:39,675 --> 01:01:41,595
- Richard?
- It's for you.

917
01:01:42,554 --> 01:01:44,394
- Gwen.
- Hi.

918
01:01:45,433 --> 01:01:47,272
What are you doing here?

919
01:01:47,672 --> 01:01:50,351
I just came by to talk to Bernie.
I didn't get a chance to last night, so...

920
01:01:51,431 --> 01:01:54,269
Oh, no. Bernie and I
are in a very big business meeting.

921
01:01:54,349 --> 01:01:55,549
- Now?
- Yes.

922
01:01:55,589 --> 01:01:58,588
Bernie has such little time,
so can you come back later?

923
01:01:58,628 --> 01:02:01,386
Wait a minute.
What happened to Mr. Romantic?

924
01:02:01,466 --> 01:02:05,425
- Candlelight? Flowers?
- I know. But Bernie is tied up right now.

925
01:02:07,824 --> 01:02:10,383
- It's a bad time.
- What is going on, Richard?

926
01:02:10,463 --> 01:02:12,822
Okay. I'll tell you.

927
01:02:12,902 --> 01:02:15,461
I probably shouldn't,
I know I shouldn't, but...

928
01:02:15,541 --> 01:02:18,499
at this point, why not? Mr. Lomax is...

929
01:02:27,136 --> 01:02:30,095
my boss. I work for him
at the insurance company.

930
01:02:33,253 --> 01:02:35,252
Bernie, you're starting to peel.

931
01:02:35,492 --> 01:02:37,651
Better get you out of the sun, huh?

932
01:02:39,731 --> 01:02:41,050
Here we go.

933
01:02:45,208 --> 01:02:47,767
We were really looking forward
to coming out here...

934
01:02:47,847 --> 01:02:49,766
when we got here, Mr. Lomax...

935
01:02:50,406 --> 01:02:51,766
Bernie was...

936
01:02:53,925 --> 01:02:54,924
dead.

937
01:02:57,323 --> 01:02:58,403
Dead.

938
01:02:58,603 --> 01:03:01,761
Like your mother and father were dead.
And your aunt is dead, too?

939
01:03:01,841 --> 01:03:02,841
Different kind of dead.

940
01:03:16,035 --> 01:03:18,514
You son of a bitch. I got you.

941
01:03:23,592 --> 01:03:27,151
Then how come I saw Bernie
with you and your friend at the party?

942
01:03:28,470 --> 01:03:30,110
Because...

943
01:03:32,469 --> 01:03:34,028
You don't believe me?

944
01:03:35,867 --> 01:03:38,346
Okay, I'm gonna prove it to you. Come on.

945
01:03:38,506 --> 01:03:39,946
This is not going to be fun.

946
01:03:50,141 --> 01:03:52,300
I know you think I'm crazy, but...

947
01:03:57,058 --> 01:03:58,058
Well?

948
01:03:59,617 --> 01:04:00,977
Where is Bernie?

949
01:04:01,497 --> 01:04:02,736
Oh, hello.

950
01:04:03,776 --> 01:04:05,975
- Where's Bernie?
- He went for more daiquiri mix.

951
01:04:06,055 --> 01:04:07,334
No, he didn't.

952
01:04:07,414 --> 01:04:10,213
Richard, I don't know what
this game is you're playing...

953
01:04:10,293 --> 01:04:12,012
but this is ridiculous.

954
01:04:12,092 --> 01:04:14,851
- I'm out of here.
- Gwen, I'm not playing any games with you.

955
01:04:14,931 --> 01:04:17,410
I'm telling you the truth! Bernie is here.

956
01:04:18,809 --> 01:04:20,569
Where is Bernie?

957
01:04:20,649 --> 01:04:23,328
What, you bastard, did you do with Bernie?

958
01:04:27,926 --> 01:04:29,645
I'm phoning the police.

959
01:04:35,962 --> 01:04:38,761
There's no dial tone. With 97 buttons...

960
01:04:40,640 --> 01:04:43,639
{y:i}- Where is your house?
- Where is the off button?

961
01:04:43,719 --> 01:04:46,678
{y:i}Look, Paulie, just don't kill them
{y:i}while I'm around.

962
01:04:46,918 --> 01:04:49,876
{y:i}- Bernie, we're on a phone here.
{y:i}- You're right.

963
01:04:49,916 --> 01:04:52,435
- Play that back.
- I just got it stopped.

964
01:04:52,515 --> 01:04:54,115
Play it back, please.

965
01:04:55,234 --> 01:04:58,353
{y:i}Hey, Lomax, it's Paulie.
{y:i}I just got to the island.

966
01:04:58,913 --> 01:04:59,872
{y:i}You're early.

967
01:04:59,952 --> 01:05:02,351
{y:i}Those two schmucks
{y:i}won't come until the 6:00 ferry...

968
01:05:02,391 --> 01:05:05,110
{y:i}- and I still have to plant the note.
