1215
01:19:43,785 --> 01:19:45,225
You broke my watch.

1216
01:19:45,584 --> 01:19:46,944
Mine still works.

1217
01:19:47,024 --> 01:19:49,223
You better put that thing
back on the dead body.

1218
01:19:49,303 --> 01:19:50,982
Drive the boat, Richard.

1219
01:19:51,062 --> 01:19:54,061
The cops are gonna take
our fat heads to jail.

1220
01:19:54,501 --> 01:19:57,339
My God. Look at them.

1221
01:19:57,379 --> 01:19:59,059
Ladies, how are you?

1222
01:19:59,459 --> 01:20:01,898
Hello, Betty.

1223
01:20:02,058 --> 01:20:04,976
God! Just once, I'd like a woman like that.

1224
01:20:05,296 --> 01:20:06,376
Let's party.

1225
01:20:12,333 --> 01:20:14,093
Turn the boat.

1226
01:20:17,491 --> 01:20:19,370
Watch the fishermen.

1227
01:20:26,527 --> 01:20:28,726
- Watch the wake!
- Duck!

1228
01:20:28,806 --> 01:20:30,486
Watch the wake, Richard!

1229
01:20:40,082 --> 01:20:42,041
This is tougher than it looks.

1230
01:20:42,161 --> 01:20:44,080
You're doing very well, Richard.

1231
01:20:44,160 --> 01:20:46,279
- Sorry I snapped at you.
- It's okay.

1232
01:20:46,359 --> 01:20:48,678
I've never been chased by a killer before.

1233
01:20:48,718 --> 01:20:51,077
It's all right. You're doing very well.

1234
01:20:52,876 --> 01:20:55,955
- Why is everybody waving at us?
- I'm popular.

1235
01:20:56,035 --> 01:20:57,035
I see.

1236
01:20:57,115 --> 01:20:59,074
Hey, Bernie, showing off again?

1237
01:21:01,993 --> 01:21:04,711
Oh, God. What the hell are those things?

1238
01:21:05,551 --> 01:21:08,310
Those are obviously channel markers.

1239
01:21:08,790 --> 01:21:09,789
Obviously.

1240
01:21:09,869 --> 01:21:12,788
Okay, wise ass, do you know
what side I'm supposed to pass on?

1241
01:21:12,868 --> 01:21:15,747
That I don't know. Just stay close.
What else can happen here?

1242
01:21:15,787 --> 01:21:17,146
I've got no idea.

1243
01:21:17,746 --> 01:21:20,225
- Serpentine.
- Is that close enough?

1244
01:21:21,904 --> 01:21:23,504
Do you hear something?

1245
01:21:25,343 --> 01:21:27,022
- There it's again.
- Yeah.

1246
01:21:27,462 --> 01:21:29,741
- I wonder what that is.
- What is that?

1247
01:21:35,539 --> 01:21:37,218
- Man overboard.
- What?

1248
01:21:37,298 --> 01:21:38,577
Stop the boat.

1249
01:21:41,696 --> 01:21:43,216
He's got nice form.

1250
01:21:47,694 --> 01:21:49,733
- I don't know.
- I'm trying to drive a boat.

1251
01:21:49,813 --> 01:21:52,652
- You're doing well.
- Trying to get us off this island of hell.

1252
01:21:52,692 --> 01:21:54,771
You had maybe one job to do.
Watch a dead body.

1253
01:21:54,851 --> 01:21:57,330
- Well, let's not argue about it.
- Jesus.

1254
01:21:58,449 --> 01:22:01,448
- You were the one who tied him up.
- Don't blame this all on me.

1255
01:22:01,528 --> 01:22:03,567
- Oh, my God.
- What?

1256
01:22:04,007 --> 01:22:05,726
You've lost my sunglasses.

1257
01:22:21,839 --> 01:22:23,319
What are you doing?

1258
01:22:24,758 --> 01:22:26,278
I haven't got a clue.

1259
01:22:27,957 --> 01:22:29,476
I don't believe this.

1260
01:22:29,996 --> 01:22:31,156
What?

1261
01:22:33,155 --> 01:22:34,474
We're out of gas.

1262
01:22:37,433 --> 01:22:39,912
Paddling in the Atlantic Ocean...

1263
01:22:40,192 --> 01:22:42,791
- on a dead body.
- I'm getting swimmer's ear.

1264
01:22:42,991 --> 01:22:44,990
This is now the perfect weekend.

1265
01:22:45,270 --> 01:22:49,468
It started when I almost broke my leg
jumping on a moving ferry.

1266
01:22:49,828 --> 01:22:53,666
I get to this beautiful beach and my host...
Sorry, he's dead.

1267
01:22:55,745 --> 01:22:57,065
Hampton Island.

1268
01:22:58,824 --> 01:23:01,343
Checkers. Excuse me, sir.
Is this your launch?

1269
01:23:01,423 --> 01:23:03,662
- Come on, let's go.
- Don't rush.

1270
01:23:06,781 --> 01:23:08,260
Come on.

1271
01:23:08,340 --> 01:23:11,459
- Can you put a little snap in it, fellows?
- Okay, Cappy.

1272
01:23:17,017 --> 01:23:18,776
Hold on, you damn fool.

1273
01:23:19,056 --> 01:23:22,734
I fell down a lighthouse.
I had a corpse wash up...

1274
01:23:22,814 --> 01:23:24,134
next to me on the shore.

1275
01:23:24,214 --> 01:23:28,492
And then I find out that my dead boss
is not only a thief, he wants to kill me.

1276
01:23:34,489 --> 01:23:35,809
I almost drown.

1277
01:23:36,009 --> 01:23:38,887
The girl of my dreams
now thinks I'm a raving lunatic.

1278
01:23:38,967 --> 01:23:40,767
You mean what's-her-name?

1279
01:23:41,686 --> 01:23:44,205
And, now, we're going back
to the house of death.

1280
01:23:44,285 --> 01:23:46,444
- Great weekend, huh?
- Great weekend!

1281
01:23:47,484 --> 01:23:50,003
Just get here as fast as you can.
Thanks, Ed.

1282
01:23:50,243 --> 01:23:51,282
Police is on the way.

1283
01:23:51,362 --> 01:23:53,921
Can just lock ourselves in
until they get here?

1284
01:23:54,001 --> 01:23:56,400
I hate it when he stares at me like that.

1285
01:23:56,480 --> 01:23:57,800
Let's go.

1286
01:24:00,478 --> 01:24:02,158
Put him in his bathroom.

1287
01:24:05,556 --> 01:24:08,195
- Bernie's picked up a little weight.
- What do you expect?

1288
01:24:08,275 --> 01:24:10,274
He's been soaking in the ocean
for two hours.

1289
01:24:10,354 --> 01:24:11,714
Made a damn good float though.

1290
01:24:16,552 --> 01:24:17,991
Are you in here?

1291
01:24:32,385 --> 01:24:33,825
It's Gwen.

1292
01:24:35,344 --> 01:24:36,583
Hi, Gwen.

1293
01:24:36,623 --> 01:24:39,382
You've got to be the weirdest guy
I've ever met.

1294
01:24:39,982 --> 01:24:42,021
You told me Bernie was dead, right?

1295
01:24:42,101 --> 01:24:43,940
I just saw you with him.

1296
01:24:44,020 --> 01:24:46,060
What's your explanation this time?

1297
01:24:46,140 --> 01:24:48,179
I don't mean to be rude,
but get the hell out of here.

1298
01:24:48,778 --> 01:24:51,017
No, I'm not going anywhere
until you tell me what is going on.

1299
01:24:51,097 --> 01:24:52,097
Listen to me!

1300
01:24:52,177 --> 01:24:55,456
You're in danger here,
leave unless you want to get shot.

1301
01:24:56,455 --> 01:24:59,214
Lomax is dead,
somebody is trying to kill us.

1302
01:24:59,294 --> 01:25:02,293
Can we stay at your house
until the cops come or what?

1303
01:25:04,692 --> 01:25:06,211
It's just Bernie.

1304
01:25:09,930 --> 01:25:13,048
Gwen, listen to me.

1305
01:25:13,128 --> 01:25:16,207
We didn't do this to him.
Do we look like we could kill someone?

1306
01:25:16,287 --> 01:25:18,526
Honey, have a drink, relax. You'll be fine.

1307
01:25:18,566 --> 01:25:21,325
Let me rephrase that.
Do I look like I could kill someone?

1308
01:25:21,405 --> 01:25:23,124
What is going on in there?

1309
01:25:27,882 --> 01:25:30,761
- Which one of you bastards hit me?
- Son of a bitch.

1310
01:25:32,400 --> 01:25:34,519
You want to get your butt kicked?

1311
01:25:39,597 --> 01:25:40,877
I can explain.

1312
01:25:57,350 --> 01:25:58,629
Company.

1313
01:26:02,068 --> 01:26:04,867
I didn't see anything.
I was looking at my watch.

1314
01:26:05,507 --> 01:26:06,666
I'm blind.

1315
01:26:14,823 --> 01:26:16,102
It's empty.

1316
01:26:17,182 --> 01:26:19,421
That's right. But this ain't.

1317
01:26:23,539 --> 01:26:24,579
Run!

1318
01:26:24,739 --> 01:26:25,938
Move it! This way!

1319
01:26:29,177 --> 01:26:30,176
It's locked.

1320
01:26:30,256 --> 01:26:32,655
What are you doing?
We're friends of Bernie's.

1321
01:26:32,735 --> 01:26:34,415
I hate Bernie's friends.

1322
01:26:40,052 --> 01:26:41,052
This way.

1323
01:26:42,011 --> 01:26:43,491
To the bedroom.

1324
01:26:44,730 --> 01:26:46,809
Come on, let's go. Up.

1325
01:26:47,049 --> 01:26:49,488
You're dead meat, you little bastards.

1326
01:26:54,206 --> 01:26:55,806
Now I'm really mad!

1327
01:26:56,325 --> 01:26:57,685
Wait.

1328
01:26:57,765 --> 01:27:01,243
- What?
- You take Gwen, you go hide...

1329
01:27:01,323 --> 01:27:04,402
I'll let him chase me,
you try and call the cops, okay?

1330
01:27:04,642 --> 01:27:06,961
Okay? That's it? No arguments?

1331
01:27:07,881 --> 01:27:10,160
I'll get you all, one by one.

1332
01:27:10,280 --> 01:27:12,399
There's no place to hide.

1333
01:27:27,153 --> 01:27:28,752
I'm gonna die.

1334
01:27:44,425 --> 01:27:46,944
You kicked me, you bastard.

1335
01:27:49,223 --> 01:27:50,943
Shit! Out of bullets.

1336
01:28:21,530 --> 01:28:22,929
Sit the hell down.

1337
01:28:27,288 --> 01:28:28,607
Hang on, Lar.

1338
01:28:30,926 --> 01:28:33,565
- Coming.
- I got him.

1339
01:28:37,763 --> 01:28:38,923
Get off.

1340
01:28:39,523 --> 01:28:41,242
- Hang on, Lar.
- I got him.

1341
01:28:41,522 --> 01:28:45,200
Stand up. Fight like a man.
Come on. Put them up, you chicken.

1342
01:28:48,799 --> 01:28:50,278
Watch this, Richard.

1343
01:28:58,075 --> 01:28:59,594
All right, Lar.

1344
01:29:06,671 --> 01:29:08,431
Fists of steel.

1345
01:29:10,590 --> 01:29:12,269
Bernie, let go of me.

1346
01:29:13,109 --> 01:29:14,868
I always liked you, Bernie.

1347
01:29:19,306 --> 01:29:20,665
I got it, thanks.

1348
01:29:20,825 --> 01:29:23,304
Just a little closer. Just get the two of us.

1349
01:29:23,384 --> 01:29:25,184
Get the handshake in, okay?

1350
01:29:25,423 --> 01:29:29,262
Wait a minute. I think I blinked. Did I blink?
I think I blinked a second there.

1351
01:29:29,342 --> 01:29:31,501
- He blinked.
- He blinked. I saw him.

1352
01:29:31,581 --> 01:29:33,140
Make sure he's wrapped up good.

1353
01:29:33,220 --> 01:29:34,460
Wait a minute.

1354
01:29:37,259 --> 01:29:39,338
I didn't kill him. He's not dead.

1355
01:29:40,137 --> 01:29:41,657
I tried to kill him.

1356
01:29:43,096 --> 01:29:44,775
Look at him. He's alive.

1357
01:29:45,295 --> 01:29:47,574
- He's not dead. He's alive.
- Move it.

1358
01:29:47,614 --> 01:29:49,573
That man is alive!

1359
01:29:50,733 --> 01:29:51,813
Now what?

1360
01:29:53,172 --> 01:29:54,691
Now I'm gonna take a week off.

1361
01:29:54,771 --> 01:29:57,730
You're taking a vacation?
The man who won't take a coffee break?

1362
01:29:57,810 --> 01:30:00,369
Gwen just invited me to stay with her.
What should I say?

1363
01:30:00,449 --> 01:30:03,768
You're kidding me. You invited him?
You fool. That's fabulous.

1364
01:30:03,808 --> 01:30:05,967
You deserve it, Richard.
The company owes you.

1365
01:30:06,047 --> 01:30:08,366
Just a couple of days
until Gwen leaves for school.

1366
01:30:08,446 --> 01:30:11,164
There's plenty of room
if you want to stay, Lar.

1367
01:30:12,524 --> 01:30:15,962
Me? Oh, no, thanks.
I'll just tough it out here at Bernie's.

1368
01:30:16,042 --> 01:30:19,201
I hear the party Saturday night is
better than Friday, actually.

1369
01:30:24,439 --> 01:30:25,758
What is going on?

1370
01:30:26,438 --> 01:30:29,597
- What's happened?
- Didn't you hear? Bernie Lomax got killed.

1371
01:30:29,677 --> 01:30:30,996
- No.
- Yeah.

1372
01:30:31,076 --> 01:30:33,515
- Did you go to that party last night?
- No.

1373
01:30:33,715 --> 01:30:36,154
Lawrence, you done real good.
I'm proud of you.

1374
01:30:36,474 --> 01:30:39,433
Yeah, I did okay, huh? Surprised myself.

1375
01:30:40,512 --> 01:30:42,072
You did great, Rich.

1376
01:30:50,348 --> 01:30:53,307
Hi, Bernie. See you at the party tonight.

1377
01:30:53,867 --> 01:30:55,066
What?

1378
01:30:56,905 --> 01:30:59,105
What did she say?

1379
01:31:05,942 --> 01:31:08,101
Mister, can I bury you?

1380
01:31:10,100 --> 01:31:11,140
Great!

